description: The new rules, broadly similar to the spring lockdown, are due to last for six weeks.
title: Coronavirus: Republic of Ireland to move to highest restrictions
title_page: Coronavirus: Republic of Ireland to move to highest restrictions - BBC News
maintext: The thinking is - put in place these measures now until the end of November and then the reward that's being held up is that if people stick to the restrictions, then maybe they can have a more normal Christmas than would previously have been possible.
